question: What is the population of Central Greece?
gold_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>

PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?population WHERE { <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Central_Greece_(region)> y2geoo:hasGAG_Population ?population }
generated_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT ?population WHERE {
  <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/gadmentity_Central_Greece_GRC.8.1_1> ?p ?population .
  FILTER(CONTAINS(LCASE(STR(?p)), "population"))
}

PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>

PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
ASK WHERE { yago:geoentity_Limerick_City_and_County_Council_11611445 geo:hasGeometry ?tgeom . ?tgeom geo:asWKT ?twkt . yago:geoentity_Waterford_City_and_County_Council_11611446 geo:hasGeometry ?ageom . ?ageom geo:asWKT ?awkt . yago:Dublin geo:hasGeometry ?igeom . ?igeom geo:asWKT ?iwkt FILTER ( geof:distance(?twkt, ?awkt, uom:metre) < geof:distance(?iwkt, ?awkt, uom:metre) ) }

PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
ASK WHERE {
  <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/gadmentity_Limerick_IRL.13_1> geo:hasGeometry ?limerickGeo .
  ?limerickGeo geo:asWKT ?limerickWKT .

  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Dublin> geo:hasGeometry ?dublinGeo .
  ?dublinGeo geo:asWKT ?dublinWKT .

  <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Waterford,_California> geo:hasGeometry ?waterfordGeo .

    geof:distance(?limerickWKT, ?dublinWKT, <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/metre>)

question: Which States of the US border with at most 2 other States?
gold_query:

PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>

PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?state WHERE { yago:United_States geo:hasGeometry ?usGeo . ?usGeo geo:asWKT ?usWKT . ?state rdf:type y2geoo:GADM_2ndOrder_AdministrativeUnit ; geo:hasGeometry ?sGeo . ?sGeo geo:asWKT ?sWKT . ?state2 rdf:type y2geoo:GADM_2ndOrder_AdministrativeUnit ; geo:hasGeometry ?s2Geo . ?s2Geo geo:asWKT ?s2WKT FILTER ( ( ( ( ?state != ?state2 ) && geof:sfWithin(?sWKT, ?usWKT) ) && geof:sfWithin(?s2WKT, ?usWKT) ) && geof:sfTouches(?sWKT, ?s2WKT) ) } GROUP BY ?state HAVING ( COUNT(?state2) <= 2 )

  ?bay <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_bay> .
  
  # Village touches or intersects bay

    ?village <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#sfIntersects> ?bay .

  # Bay intersects or overlaps Peloponnese region

    ?bay <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#sfIntersects> <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/gadmentity_Peloponnese_GRC.7.2_1> .
  } UNION {
    ?bay <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#sfOverlaps> <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/gadmentity_Peloponnese_GRC.7.2_1> .
  }
  
  # Get geometries
  ?village <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?villageGeo .
  ?villageGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?villageWKT .
  
  ?bay <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?bayGeo .
  ?bayGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?bayWKT .
  
  # Filter villages west of bays
  FILTER (strdf:left(?villageWKT, ?bayWKT))
}

PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?village WHERE { <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/Peloponnese_(region)> geo:hasGeometry ?o . ?o geo:asWKT ?geoWKT . ?village rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_village ; geo:hasGeometry ?o1 . ?o1 geo:asWKT ?geoWKT1 . ?beach rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_beach ; geo:hasGeometry ?o2 . ?o2 geo:asWKT ?geoWKT2 FILTER ( ( strdf:within(?geoWKT1, ?geoWKT) && strdf:within(?geoWKT2, ?geoWKT) ) && strdf:below(?geoWKT1, ?geoWKT2) ) }
generated_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?village ?villageWKT WHERE {
  # Peloponnese geometry
  <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/gadmentity_Peloponnese_GRC.7.2_1> geo:hasGeometry ?peloponneseGeo .
  ?peloponneseGeo geo:asWKT ?peloponneseWKT .

  # Beaches in Peloponnese
  ?beach rdf:type <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_beach> .
  ?beach geo:hasGeometry ?beachGeo .
  ?beachGeo geo:asWKT ?beachWKT .

  # Beach intersects or is within Peloponnese
  FILTER (
    strdf:sfIntersects(?beachWKT, ?peloponneseWKT) || strdf:sfWithin(?beachWKT, ?peloponneseWKT)
  )

  # Villages
  ?village rdf:type <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_village> .
  ?village geo:hasGeometry ?villageGeo .
  ?villageGeo geo:asWKT ?villageWKT .

  # Village is south of beach
  FILTER (strdf:below(?villageWKT, ?beachWKT))
}

  ?region <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?regionGeo .

  ?forest <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?forestGeo .
  ?forestGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?forestWKT .
  
  # Region of type GAG_Region and its geometry

  ?region <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#hasGeometry> ?regionGeo .

  ?county <http://www.opengis.net/geo/hasGeometry> ?countyGeo .

  ?parkGeo <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#asWKT> ?parkWKT .

PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT ?DistrictWard) AS ?wards) WHERE { ?District rdf:type y2geoo:OS_District ; geo:hasGeometry ?geomL . ?geomL geo:asWKT ?A . ?DistrictWard rdf:type y2geoo:OS_DistrictWard ; geo:hasGeometry ?geom . ?geom geo:asWKT ?B FILTER geof:sfWithin(?B, ?A) }

PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>

PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>

  ?ward <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#sfWithin> ?district .

  ?state a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/State> .

  ?stateGeo geo:asWKT ?stateWKT .

    ?lake a <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_lake> .
    ?lake geo:hasGeometry ?lakeGeo .
    ?lakeGeo geo:asWKT ?lakeWKT .

    ?canal geo:hasGeometry ?canalGeo .
    ?canalGeo geo:asWKT ?canalWKT .
    FILTER(geof:sfWithin(?canalWKT, ?stateWKT))
  }
}

PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT ?city WHERE { yago:England geo:hasGeometry ?eGeo . ?eGeo geo:asWKT ?eWKT . ?city rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_city ; geo:hasGeometry ?cGeo . ?cGeo geo:asWKT ?cWKT . ?lake rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_lake ; geo:hasGeometry ?lGeo . ?lGeo geo:asWKT ?lWKT FILTER ( geof:sfWithin(?cWKT, ?eWKT) && strdf:touches(?cWKT, ?lWKT) ) } GROUP BY ?city ORDER BY DESC(COUNT(?lake)) LIMIT 1

  ?city <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#sfTouches> ?lake .
  ?lake <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/OSM_lake> .
  ?city <http://www.opengis.net/geo#hasGeometry> ?cityGeo .
  ?cityGeo <http://www.opengis.net/geo#asWKT> ?cityWKT .
}
GROUP BY ?city ?cityWKT

LIMIT 1

question: What is the largest forest in Texas by area?
gold_query:
PREFIX geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#>
PREFIX geof: <http://www.opengis.net/def/function/geosparql/>
PREFIX strdf: <http://strdf.di.uoa.gr/ontology#>
PREFIX uom: <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX yago: <http://yago-knowledge.org/resource/>
PREFIX y2geor: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/resource/>
PREFIX y2geoo: <http://kr.di.uoa.gr/yago2geo/ontology/>
SELECT ?forest (strdf:area(?fWKT) AS ?farea) WHERE { yago:Texas geo:hasGeometry ?usGeo . ?usGeo geo:asWKT ?usWKT . ?forest rdf:type y2geoo:OSM_forest ; geo:hasGeometry ?fGeo . ?fGeo geo:asWKT ?fWKT FILTER geof:sfWithin(?fWKT, ?usWKT) } ORDER BY DESC(?farea) LIMIT 1
